<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-10-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="39" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Harris</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-10-14"><hi rend="italic">October 14,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 44.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 42, of the 21st ultimo, reporting your refusal to issue a
                            passport to Mrs. Elenora Eisenschimmel.</p>
                        <p>The Department approves your action in the matter.</p>
                        <p>Your remarks in reference to applicants for passports who fail to fulfill
                            their declared intention to return to the United States are very
                            sensible and indicate the proper course to be followed in such
                            cases.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>